& S_{n}+\frac{1}{3} S_{3 n}=\frac{4 a_{1}+d(4 n-2)}{2} \cdot n=\frac{2 a_{1}+d(2 n-2)}{2} \cdot 2 n=S_{2 n}
\end{aligned}
$$

This completes the proof.

